{"lessons": [{"id": "l1", "title": "Thrust-to-Weight Ratio", "body": "A drone needs thrust greater than its weight to fly. Cinematic drones aim for 2:1 for smooth flight, but racing drones aim for 5:1 or higher for instant punch-outs!"}, {"id": "l2", "title": "Battery Voltage (Cells)", "body": "LiPo batteries are made of 'Cells' (S). A 4S battery is 14.8V, while a 6S is 22.2V. More voltage means motors spin faster, but your ESC must be rated to handle it!"}, {"id": "l3", "title": "Propeller Pitch & Size", "body": "Larger props generate more lift efficiently but take longer to change speed. If you put 7-inch props on a 5-inch frame, they will hit each other!"}, {"id": "l4", "title": "The Brains: FC", "body": "The Flight Controller loops thousands of times a second, reading the gyroscope to keep the drone level. Complex tasks like GPS rescue require faster processors like an F7."}]}